1
00:01:43,458 --> 00:01:45,625
Time to get
baked, little dude...

2
00:01:45,708 --> 00:01:47,750
Oh no. You're
in sweet potato hell!

3
00:01:48,625 --> 00:01:51,291
Banba! When you bake a sweet
potato, aren't you supposed to

4
00:01:51,375 --> 00:01:54,250
put it on the wood before
you light the fire? Hah?

5
00:01:54,333 --> 00:01:56,458
No worries.
I'm a pro at this.

6
00:01:56,916 --> 00:01:57,750
Huh?

7
00:01:58,791 --> 00:02:00,583
Fro-mageddon!
Fro-mageddoooon!

8
00:02:00,666 --> 00:02:04,416
Hey Mom. The Sisterhood and
I put together a little bonfire

9
00:02:04,500 --> 00:02:06,916
and baked some sweet potatoes
from Dad's farm this afternoon.

10
00:02:07,000 --> 00:02:08,750
Crisis averted.

11
00:02:08,833 --> 00:02:10,125
For now!

12
00:02:10,208 --> 00:02:11,875
That smells good.

13
00:02:11,958 --> 00:02:15,208
You and me and Dad... we
used to have bonfires a bunch,

14
00:02:15,291 --> 00:02:19,125
didn't we?
Yeah... like that day...

15
00:02:19,875 --> 00:02:23,250
Hey, sweetie, wanna help
me gather some firewood?

16
00:02:23,333 --> 00:02:24,541
Yeah!

17
00:02:24,625 --> 00:02:26,500
Don't push yourself
too hard, okay?

18
00:02:26,583 --> 00:02:28,958
I'll take it easy, I promise.

19
00:02:29,041 --> 00:02:30,833
Lookit, Mommy! Look!

20
00:02:31,333 --> 00:02:34,541
I found some driftwood. There's
a whole bunch of it over here!

21
00:02:34,625 --> 00:02:36,083
I'm gonna bring
it back to Daddy,

22
00:02:36,166 --> 00:02:38,750
'cause he makes
really good fires with it!

23
00:02:40,750 --> 00:02:43,166
When'd you get so smart, baby?

24
00:02:44,041 --> 00:02:48,958
I a'member the one Daddy
made last time! Wow, look!

25
00:02:49,041 --> 00:02:52,125
That's the biggest driftwood
in the whole worl--!

26
00:02:53,541 --> 00:02:55,083
Mommy...?

27
00:02:58,458 --> 00:03:01,541
Another minute or two
and they should be done!

28
00:03:03,583 --> 00:03:05,625
I know it was years ago,

29
00:03:05,708 --> 00:03:08,375
but it feels like
it was just yesterday.

30
00:03:09,166 --> 00:03:13,458
Something reminds me
of you, and I start to cry.

31
00:03:13,541 --> 00:03:17,666
Days like this, I just
wanna watch the jellyfish.

32
00:03:23,916 --> 00:03:26,875
The more established restaurants
and kimono fabric shops

33
00:03:26,958 --> 00:03:29,458
oppose the
redevelopment plans.

34
00:03:30,000 --> 00:03:31,708
That's something
to keep an eye on.

35
00:03:31,791 --> 00:03:33,166
Hey, bro!

36
00:03:33,250 --> 00:03:35,625
What have I told you
about barging into my room?

37
00:03:35,708 --> 00:03:37,416
I broke into
the old man's room.

38
00:03:37,500 --> 00:03:39,833
Come on, searching
the house again?

39
00:03:39,916 --> 00:03:44,041
Yeah... But I still didn't
find Mom's address anywhere.

40
00:03:44,125 --> 00:03:48,041
Sucks to be you. Holed up in
here, working on your day off...

41
00:03:49,416 --> 00:03:50,500
What's this?

42
00:03:52,000 --> 00:03:54,416
Oh... Redevelopment plans
for your friend's building.

43
00:03:54,500 --> 00:03:56,458
Probably a high-rise hotel.

44
00:03:57,791 --> 00:03:59,333
Listen up!

45
00:03:59,416 --> 00:04:02,000
Hands off the starchy
carbs, girls! This is no time

46
00:04:02,083 --> 00:04:05,083
for sweet potatoes!
Feast your eyes on these!

47
00:04:05,500 --> 00:04:08,833
Top-secret documents! This
block is getting a facelift!

48
00:04:08,916 --> 00:04:11,625
Two years from now,
it'll be a ritzy hotel!

49
00:04:11,708 --> 00:04:13,750
What's this all about?

50
00:04:13,833 --> 00:04:16,000
A ritzy... hotel?

51
00:04:22,916 --> 00:04:25,625
Hey! I never lived
anywhere ritzy!

52
00:04:25,708 --> 00:04:26,416
Right?

53
00:04:26,500 --> 00:04:27,958
Oh my, yes!

54
00:04:28,041 --> 00:04:30,500
Wise up! You five ain't gonna
be living in the damn hotel!

55
00:04:30,583 --> 00:04:33,083
Without this building, you're
all screwed! You're a bunch of

56
00:04:33,166 --> 00:04:36,166
NEETs, remember?! Who's gonna
rent apartments to you guys?!

57
00:04:36,250 --> 00:04:38,500
No jobs, no references?!
Not gonna happen!

58
00:04:38,583 --> 00:04:40,166
And I don't want to see
an awesomely retro place

59
00:04:40,250 --> 00:04:42,208
like this bite the dust!

60
00:04:42,291 --> 00:04:45,875
It shall endure! The Nunnery
must live on when all of us

61
00:04:45,958 --> 00:04:49,500
are dust! God may forgive its
destruction but I never will!

62
00:04:49,583 --> 00:04:52,666
Do calm down, Mayaya! It's
still in the planning stages,

63
00:04:52,750 --> 00:04:55,416
and folks're already
protesting against it!

64
00:04:55,500 --> 00:04:57,791
Wait, you knew, what was up?

65
00:04:57,875 --> 00:05:01,791
Duh. Even we read the
neighborhood newsletter, Meat.

66
00:05:01,875 --> 00:05:03,291
We do live here.

67
00:05:03,375 --> 00:05:06,541
Don't cry anymore. Please,
Mayaya! Just try to remain cal--

68
00:05:06,625 --> 00:05:08,541
"Better to wrong the
world than have it wrong me!"

69
00:05:08,625 --> 00:05:10,625
by the brave warlord Tsao Tsao.

70
00:05:14,125 --> 00:05:16,291
Don't know why I expected
a sensible response

71
00:05:16,375 --> 00:05:17,708
out of any of 'em.

72
00:05:17,791 --> 00:05:22,750
Could you please go home
already? Like I ask every time.

73
00:05:23,208 --> 00:05:27,750
I'm heading out for a bit so
you. Should. Go. Home. Now...

74
00:05:27,833 --> 00:05:30,500
You, go out?
Who'd a thunk! Shopping?

75
00:05:30,583 --> 00:05:33,958
No... to an aquarium...
for the jellyfish...

76
00:05:34,041 --> 00:05:36,000
Oh, I'm not busy.
I'll tag along!

77
00:05:36,083 --> 00:05:39,708
Huh?! No, no you don't wanna
do that! It's like an hour away!

78
00:05:39,791 --> 00:05:43,458
Y'know the Enoshima Aquarium
in Shonan? It's that one!

79
00:05:43,541 --> 00:05:46,041
If we go by car we'll
be there in no time!

80
00:05:46,125 --> 00:05:48,708
Let's take my brother's
Benz. Driver included!

81
00:05:48,791 --> 00:05:50,125
Huh?!

82
00:05:50,208 --> 00:05:52,500
We'll get ya all Cinderella'd
up, just like before!

83
00:05:52,583 --> 00:05:55,833
Tsukimi, hon? Could I
grab another sweet potato?

84
00:05:58,125 --> 00:06:00,291
Tip of the
iceberg, ladies!

85
00:06:00,375 --> 00:06:03,041
Sick! And we can
borrow any one of 'em?!

86
00:06:04,166 --> 00:06:06,583
My dear girl! I am so
glad you've awakened to

87
00:06:06,666 --> 00:06:08,625
the wonders of the kimono!

88
00:06:08,708 --> 00:06:11,291
Hey! This one's
got a cute pattern!

89
00:06:12,291 --> 00:06:14,208
You have good eye!

90
00:06:14,291 --> 00:06:16,708
That's an heirloom obi from
the early Showa period that

91
00:06:16,791 --> 00:06:19,708
I discovered in this kimono
shop in Nishiogi I frequent--

92
00:06:19,791 --> 00:06:21,875
It's in amazing shape
for its age, right?!

93
00:06:21,958 --> 00:06:24,125
There aren't many sashes
of this pedigree and vibrance

94
00:06:24,208 --> 00:06:27,375
in circulation anymore! This one
started life as a double-weave

95
00:06:27,458 --> 00:06:30,333
sash but was repurposed in
the Nagoya style so it could be

96
00:06:30,416 --> 00:06:32,000
worn in more casual situations.

97
00:06:32,083 --> 00:06:33,750
You can pair it
up with every pattern.

98
00:06:33,833 --> 00:06:35,750
Chieko, you're
kinda freaking me out!

99
00:06:35,833 --> 00:06:38,250
Let's shoot for the moon and
use a collar with roses, too!

100
00:06:38,333 --> 00:06:40,625
I think you should
do the honors, Chieko.

101
00:06:40,708 --> 00:06:43,083
When it comes to putting
on a kimono, this boy--

102
00:06:43,166 --> 00:06:47,541
♪Oh boy! Oh boy! I'm gonna
try on a kimono, dugga-dun!♪

103
00:06:47,625 --> 00:06:52,291
♪Dance the Kimono Samba!
Oh boy! Oh boy, oh boy!♪

104
00:06:52,375 --> 00:06:54,458
You can't keep saying
"boy" in front of them!

105
00:06:54,541 --> 00:06:56,291
Okay, okay. Chill!

106
00:06:56,375 --> 00:07:01,041
Now it is time to give yourself
to the kimono, body and soul!

107
00:07:01,833 --> 00:07:03,791
Oh, big brother!

108
00:07:05,375 --> 00:07:08,500
Do us a solid, huh?
Lend us your car?

109
00:07:11,583 --> 00:07:14,333
Didn't think you and the
Benz were a package deal.

110
00:07:14,416 --> 00:07:18,000
Hanamori's with Father. He's
golfing a round in Hakone.

111
00:07:19,416 --> 00:07:22,000
Fore!

112
00:07:26,541 --> 00:07:29,875
Excellent shot, sir.
You're on a roll today.

113
00:07:31,208 --> 00:07:33,708
Yeah, whatever! You're
only chauffeuring 'cause

114
00:07:33,791 --> 00:07:35,708
she's here with me.

115
00:07:36,333 --> 00:07:36,875
Tsukimi...

116
00:07:36,958 --> 00:07:38,958
Uh... yes...?!

117
00:07:39,041 --> 00:07:43,000
The other day... when I stopped
by to return your glasses...

118
00:07:43,083 --> 00:07:44,916
I'm sorry about how that went.

119
00:07:45,000 --> 00:07:46,291
Huh?

120
00:07:46,375 --> 00:07:49,833
I meant to hand the bag
right to you, but... well...

121
