170
00:10:46,625 --> 00:10:50,958
What the hell? Why's
she being so cute right now?

171
00:10:52,541 --> 00:10:55,666
I'm seeing her have
fun for once, is that it?

172
00:10:55,750 --> 00:10:58,916
Betcha that's a big part of
it. And, I don't think she's

173
00:10:59,000 --> 00:11:01,875
ever actually looked at
me when we're talking before.

174
00:11:09,625 --> 00:11:13,833
Why... why does
that... piss me off?

175
00:11:14,750 --> 00:11:15,666
Commercial message!

176
00:11:15,750 --> 00:11:17,083
Clara!

177
00:11:18,166 --> 00:11:19,250
Are you ready for more?

178
00:11:19,333 --> 00:11:20,666
Tequila!

179
00:11:20,750 --> 00:11:23,541
All of my life, from birth
up 'til five minutes ago,

180
00:11:23,625 --> 00:11:27,250
basically... I've always
had girls flock to me.

181
00:11:27,333 --> 00:11:30,500
My pockets? Full of business
cards. Modeling and pop idol

182
00:11:30,583 --> 00:11:34,833
agencies. Record labels. Agents
run after me on the street.

183
00:11:35,583 --> 00:11:37,916
Hottest girl in school? Check.

184
00:11:38,000 --> 00:11:40,708
Hottest girl at some
other school? Check.

185
00:11:40,791 --> 00:11:42,166
And local beauty queens?

186
00:11:42,250 --> 00:11:45,500
Oh yeah, checkity
check check check.

187
00:11:45,875 --> 00:11:49,375
I was a hit with the
ladies. Too big of a hit.

188
00:11:49,458 --> 00:11:52,666
Caused me a lot of woman
drama, and now I'm bored of 'em.

189
00:11:52,750 --> 00:11:56,166
Popularity is for chumps.
It's a pain in the ass.

190
00:11:56,833 --> 00:11:59,541
So why does this,
an awkward little hug...

191
00:11:59,625 --> 00:12:02,291
between my bro, the political
dweeb with the charisma of

192
00:12:02,375 --> 00:12:06,125
a sweet potato... and some
otaku girl with a head full of

193
00:12:06,208 --> 00:12:08,625
jellyfish who can't
even hardly see him.

194
00:12:09,333 --> 00:12:11,541
Why the hell does
it piss me off, huh?

195
00:12:11,625 --> 00:12:14,166
What do I care?!
They're both nerds!

196
00:12:14,250 --> 00:12:17,458
Yeah, no, don't care.

197
00:12:19,541 --> 00:12:22,250
Hey, guys? Hanging on
each other in public?

198
00:12:22,333 --> 00:12:25,208
Kinda tacky.
Let's wrap it up, yeah?

199
00:12:25,291 --> 00:12:26,958
Get yer paws offa her!

200
00:12:28,333 --> 00:12:31,708
Tsukimi, what are you crying
for? Come on what's wrong?

201
00:12:31,791 --> 00:12:33,916
Aw, now your makeup is a mess!

202
00:12:34,000 --> 00:12:38,375
I... I'm sorry... I'm
gonna go clean up a bit...

203
00:12:38,458 --> 00:12:41,291
Well! Don't touch your
eyes unless you gotta!

204
00:12:41,375 --> 00:12:44,708
Ahh, the mascara's waterproof,
guess it doesn't matter.

205
00:12:47,875 --> 00:12:49,250
What was that all about?

206
00:12:49,333 --> 00:12:52,083
I... I don't know...

207
00:12:52,166 --> 00:12:55,666
A likely story! Remind
me how old you are?!

208
00:12:55,750 --> 00:12:57,541
I'm... thirty...

209
00:12:57,625 --> 00:13:00,583
The heir of a famous political
family hanging all over a girl

210
00:13:00,666 --> 00:13:03,208
barely outta high
school in a public place?!

211
00:13:03,291 --> 00:13:05,250
I'm calling the tabloids, perv!

212
00:13:05,333 --> 00:13:10,250
Hold on! It wasn't like that.
She just started crying, okay?

213
00:13:10,833 --> 00:13:13,833
Out of nowhere...
I didn't know what to do.

214
00:13:13,916 --> 00:13:16,500
So I guess... I hugged her.

215
00:13:17,458 --> 00:13:20,083
She said the
jellyfish reminded her.

216
00:13:27,958 --> 00:13:32,166
Mama will still be
watching you... okay, baby?

217
00:13:32,250 --> 00:13:37,708
Up in heaven. I'll be
watching you, every day...

218
00:13:38,666 --> 00:13:43,208
Please, don't cry,
Tsukimi. I'm sorry.

219
00:13:46,250 --> 00:13:48,083
Are you all right?

220
00:13:49,208 --> 00:13:54,666
I'm sorry... These... weren't
here the last time I came...

221
00:13:56,833 --> 00:13:59,708
Uh, can you tell
me what's wrong?

222
00:13:59,791 --> 00:14:04,000
I shouldn't cry!
I promised her...

223
00:14:04,083 --> 00:14:05,375
What?

224
00:14:05,458 --> 00:14:10,458
When... my mom died... I
promised... I wouldn't cry!

225
00:14:14,166 --> 00:14:19,916
It's okay. You can
cry. Let it all out.

226
00:14:35,625 --> 00:14:37,791
I feel a little calmer.

227
00:14:39,833 --> 00:14:42,833
Wait... What just
happened back there?!

228
00:14:45,333 --> 00:14:47,000
Are you all right?

229
00:14:47,791 --> 00:14:51,791
It's okay. You can
cry. Let it all out.

230
00:14:51,875 --> 00:14:54,916
What? This can't be
right! According to these

231
00:14:55,000 --> 00:14:57,250
